    <text id="B0425T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks if Albemarle County is prepared to support Martha Butler, who will
                    be sent there from Staunton. Higgs' reply is attached as an endorsement.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="addenda" id="d4">
                <p><abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands"
                    >BRF&amp;AL</abbr>, 3rd <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 7th Sub <abbr
                        expan="District">Dist</abbr>, Charlottesville, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va.</abbr><lb/><abbr expan="Respectfully">Respfy</abbr> returned The
                    authorities are compelled to take care of their poor and if she comes she will
                    probably be provided for, that is I will see that she is, though I cant see the
                    use of sending her here. We are full <hi rend="underline">and no vacant
                    seats</hi>.<lb/>AF Higgs, <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lt</abbr>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <abbr expan="Infantry">Infty</abbr> &amp;c</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut.</abbr> A. F. Higgs, <abbr
                            expan="United States Army">U.S.A.</abbr><lb/><abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Sub Asst.
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Charlottesville</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-10"><abbr expan="February">Feb</abbr> 10 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Lieutenant</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Martha Butler (<abbr expan="colored">col'd</abbr>) and her three children are a
                    charge upon the corporation of Staunton. She belongs to the University District,
                    Albemarle <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> and the civil authorities propose to
                    send her thither. Please inform me if the civil authorities of Albemarle <abbr
                        expan="County">Co.</abbr> are prepared to receive and provide for her.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/><abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr. obt
                        servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>Thos P. Jackson<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >Asst. Sub Asst. Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
